"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response..md#CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response. This is trying to imitate the T cell receptor signalling (TCR) that happens naturally in response to invading pathogens. When designing the CAR cell, [[When designing a CAR-T cell, it is important to take into consideration the location of the target epitope in order to optimize the spacer length.]]  Advances in engineering such as [[Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity]] so that overstimulation of T-cell pathways doesn't hurt the patients. Additionally, [[Universal CAR-T cell therapeutics overcome many of the barriers to widespread application and toxicities associated with this treatment.]]{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response..md#References":true},"mtime":1709479440641,"size":1005,"hash":"25e943e85202c551a70a35d269770e17d6e99425baa9836efc147dcd36949d98"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00790097,0.00311404,-0.02092929,0.04189559,0.04005934,-0.00260512,0.01223796,-0.02889154,-0.00724462,0.00518491,-0.00779255,-0.00719634,-0.03394007,-0.04784212,0.02586889,0.00370633,0.0372644,-0.0186456,-0.01113843,-0.00797983,0.09669439,-0.01137507,-0.01034337,0.02329408,-0.06365953,-0.02395255,0.00869614,0.0054985,-0.08602701,-0.06838689,0.00393283,0.02137549,0.03205798,0.01552838,0.01899755,0.00182594,0.01666697,-0.01440051,0.01050263,-0.02947664,-0.0285546,0.00654573,0.00318095,0.00417773,0.02019536,0.04901786,0.02998573,0.00509774,-0.00587399,0.03552477,-0.0177693,-0.00828461,-0.00104166,0.0140182,-0.02440689,-0.01755007,-0.01512539,-0.03948648,-0.02551259,-0.01298504,-0.01944713,-0.01356125,-0.14476883,0.30861861,-0.01028197,0.00144528,0.00726291,-0.01631283,-0.01128194,0.16931099,0.01470925,-0.03041543,-0.00546558,0.00608976,-0.0144266,0.00513944,-0.03631586,0.01459398,0.01290427,0.00429229,0.13985473,-0.05817389,0.01877489,-0.01047895,0.03021884,-0.00563265,-0.00096059,0.01026416,-0.03476707,-0.0081328,-0.0122352,-0.00733233,0.04382998,-0.0105045,0.19720335,0.01163106,-0.02319028,-0.02645571,0.0334301,0.04701709,0.0202618,-0.01876579,-0.02165939,0.04023563,-0.0224609,0.02076383,0.01710376,0.0092144,0.03197989,-0.02635988,-0.01953224,0.00219303,-0.04784013,0.01405689,-0.00313851,0.01582024,-0.01817363,-0.01918481,-0.00034702,0.11019679,0.01198877,-0.01016699,-0.01707155,0.02055767,-0.0450233,0.07883264,-0.00057409,0.09765639,-0.01257659,0.02158834,-0.02894194,-0.00143095,0.02682694,0.019115,0.00387329,-0.02937839,0.01431186,0.02907943,-0.03583589,-0.02829126,0.00441308,-0.07887082,0.02640055,-0.10195038,0.00905669,-0.1438805,0.00625311,-0.012027,0.01705576,0.02006498,0.0080162,-0.00890896,0.01