"smart_blocks:000 Zettelkasten/CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response..md#CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response. This is trying to imitate the T cell receptor signalling (TCR) that happens naturally in response to invading pathogens. When designing the CAR cell, [[When designing a CAR-T cell, it is important to take into consideration the location of the target epitope in order to optimize the spacer length.]]  Advances in engineering such as [[Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity]] so that overstimulation of T-cell pathways doesn't hurt the patients. Additionally, [[Universal CAR-T cell therapeutics overcome many of the barriers to widespread application and toxicities associated with this treatment.]]{1}": {"class_name":"SmartBlock","embeddings":{},"path":"000 Zettelkasten/CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response..md#CAR-T cells are designed to have connect an extracellular ligand recognition domain (scFv) to the target antigen which then activates the intracellular module (CD3) to activate the T-cell immune response. This is trying to imitate the T cell receptor signalling (TCR) that happens naturally in response to invading pathogens. When designing the CAR cell, [[When designing a CAR-T cell, it is important to take into consideration the location of the target epitope in order to optimize the spacer length.]]  Advances in engineering such as [[Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of 